    <text>
        <body>

            <!-- pg 3; no facsimile -->
            <pb/>
            <div type="entry">
                <p>The wear frozen over: dozens of blackheaded gulls sitting on the snow-covered
                    ice: the buildings above the bare trees.</p>


                <p>A burn from the goaf--'steep', of an eye</p>


                <p>If the <ref target="#n1">goaf</ref> be one's heart? soul? unconscious?</p>


                <p>Muck from the goaf</p>
            </div>

            <!-- pg 4 -->
            <pb facs="bunting-nb-p4.jpg"/>
            <div type="entry">
                <lg type="poem-extract">
                    <l rend="indented">--they knew not</l>
                    <l>That what I motion<del>e</del><add>'</add>d was of God; I knew</l>
                    <l>From intimate impulse...</l>
                </lg>

                <p><ref type="bibl" target="#SA">Samson Agonistes</ref></p>

            </div>

            <milestone unit="section"/>
            <div type="entry">
                <l>A deep, booming voice, and words</l>
                <l>like flakes of snow [<persName ref="#odysseus">Odysseus</persName>]-- <ref
                        type="bibl" target="#iliad">Il<del>l</del>iad 3</ref></l>

                <p>Achilles' horses <q type="written" corresp="#iliad">are hard to master and
                        <lb/>difficult to drive.</q></p>

                <p>Turmoil of her hair––<w cert="low">Ousori</w></p>

                <p>Flowers of oak, broom, meadowsweet <lb/>= <choice>
                        <orig>Blodeuedd</orig>
                        <reg>Blodeuwedd</reg>
                    </choice>
                    <lb/>(wife of Lleu)</p>
            </div>
            <!-- pg 5 -->
            <pb facs="bunting-nb-p5.jpg"/>
            <div type="entry">
                <head>(<date>April</date>)</head>

                <lg>
                    <l>A thread net drapes and creases the <w cert="low"/>haugh,</l>
                    <l>crackled glaze fired by dexterous suns.</l>
                    <l>What use? Elegant hope, fever of tune,</l>
                    <l>new now, next, in the fall, to be dust.</l>
                </lg>

                <p><date when="1969">1969</date> ?straw?</p>

            </div>

            <milestone unit="section"/>

            <div type="entry">
                <p><ref target="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/C%C3%BA_Chulainn"><choice>
                            <orig>Cuchulainn</orig>
                            <reg>Cúchulainn</reg>
                        </choice></ref>
                    <lb/>Same story as <ref type="bibl" target="#gawain">Gawain</ref>. </p>

                <milestone unit="section"/>

                <p>My lines still the wind.</p>
            </div>

            <!-- pg 6 -->
            <pb facs="bunting-nb-pg6.jpg"/>

            <div type="entry">
                <p>1st May, <ref target="#n2"><choice>
                            <sic>Beltaine</sic>
                            <reg>Beltane</reg>
                        </choice></ref></p>
                <p>1st Nov, Semaine</p>
            </div>

            <milestone unit="section"/>

            <div type="entry">
                <head><hi rend="underlined">Money</hi></head>
                <p>It is not the primitive confusion of money with a <lb/>commodity that
                        <del>d</del> bedevils our rulers, but <lb/>the confusion between its two
                    functions, as a <lb/>means of exchange and as a unit of account.</p>
                <p>A muddled notion of this difficulty lies <lb/>behind the various theories of
                    Douglas, <ref target="#EP">Pound</ref>, and <lb/><ref target="JMK">Keynes</ref>;
                    but none of them sees the immense <lb/>difficulties the double use of money
                    creates, or <lb/>how what is perhaps good for exchange may be <lb/>ruinous to
                    accounts, and vice versa.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
